review_blob: I like the color of this lager. The cinnamon and ginger are subtle, additive but balanced. This has an nice balance of body and hops. Head retention is moderate. The warming is great for a cold day up north. This beer is easy to drinking but not overly complex.
Easy drinking ale. Nice body and feel. Not a lot of aroma, but decent for style. The color is appropriate. The taste is solid but not overwhelming. The hops are low to medium.
